HEADWORD: old-man-of-the-woods
<hw>old-man-of-the-woods</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An edible mild-tasting
mushroom (<spn>Strobilomyces floccopus</spn>) found in coniferous
woodlands of eastern North America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> old man of the woods, <spn>Strobilomyces
floccopus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oldness</ent>⟦br⟧
